cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.GR 

This paper is about deep image segmentation, which is a subfield of computer vision (cs.CV). The proposed method involves designing a continuous-valued loss function and incorporating it into end-to-end training of a deep neural network, which falls under machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The method also aims to preserve topology, which is a concept in mathematics and graph theory (cs.GR). Finally, the paper uses natural and biomedical datasets, which suggests that it may also be relevant to neuroscience (cs.NE).
